# RK8 environment — copy to .env.local for development.
# Everything here is OPTIONAL: the app boots and plays anonymously with none of
# it set. These only enable account features (contribute / moderation / sync).

# ── OAuth providers ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# A provider's "Continue with…" button only appears when its id+secret are set.
# Register apps and set the redirect URI to:
#   <APP_URL>/api/auth/callback/discord
#   <APP_URL>/api/auth/callback/google
#
# Discord:  https://discord.com/developers/applications → OAuth2 (scopes: identify, email)
DISCORD_CLIENT_ID=
DISCORD_CLIENT_SECRET=
# Google:   https://console.cloud.google.com → APIs & Services → Credentials → OAuth client (Web)
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=

# ── Dev seeded-admin fallback ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Lets you sign in as an admin with NO OAuth setup, for local dev / CI / demos.
# Hard-disabled in production builds regardless of value. Off by default.
DEV_AUTH=1
DEV_AUTH_EMAIL=admin@rk8.local
DEV_AUTH_PASSWORD=rk8admin

# Optional: override the data directory (DB + storage live here).
# RK8_DATA_DIR=

# ── Deployment / proxy ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Public base URL — used to build links in emails (DMCA notice verification).
# APP_URL=https://rk8.example

# How many trusted reverse proxies / load balancers sit in front of the app.
# Anonymous rate limiting derives the client IP by stepping in this many hops
# from the right of X-Forwarded-For; set it to match your deployment so the
# limit can't be bypassed by spoofing XFF (Vercel / single nginx = 1, the
# default; LB + ingress = 2). Set 0 only if the app is directly exposed.
# TRUSTED_PROXY_HOPS=1

# ── Email (production) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# v1 uses a dev mailer that logs to the console + writes to data/outbox/.
# Wire a real transport (Resend/SES/Postmark) in src/lib/mailer.ts before
# launch — the DMCA notice email-verification step depends on it.
